The paper deals with the stable marriage problem, which is a well-known problem in game theory and algorithms. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem under different degrees of orderedness in the preferences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some combinatorial aspects, which suggest the sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
